    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-04-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-04-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="874"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d874">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.6363 Manchuria/170</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Chief of the Division of Far Eastern
                        Affairs</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Hornbeck</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-04-10">April 10,
                            1935</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The British Ambassador called and brought me two papers relating to the
                    “Manchukuo” oil monopoly. These papers are here attached.<note n="84"
                        xml:id="d874fn84">Neither printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>I inquired of the Ambassador just what his Government contemplated in the
                    statement that it would hold the Japanese Government responsible for losses
                    which might accrue to British nationals from the unlawful action of the
                    “Manchukuo” régime. The Ambassador said that he thought they meant that they
                    would press the claims for such losses.</p>
                <p>There followed some discussion of other points in the papers and I informed the
                    Ambassador that we would give the contents of these papers immediate
                    consideration and I would communicate with him at the earliest possible
                    date.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>S[<hi rend="smallcaps">tanley</hi>] K. H[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                            >ornbeck</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
